HEADWORD: Trigamy
<hw>Trig"a*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trigamia</ets>,Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>trigamie</ets>. See
<er>Trigamous</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of marrying, or the state of
being married, three times; also, the offense of having three husbands
or three wives at the same time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

